SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT

AAR library manifest. minSdkVersion 28 is the library's hard floor (bionic
weak-symbol gate for posix_spawn used by the upstream mtmd helper — see
CLAUDE.md "Android minimum API level"); AGP enforces it against every
consuming app at merge time, so an app with a lower minSdk fails its build
instead of crashing at runtime.
-->
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    package="net.ladenthin.llama.android">
    <uses-sdk android:minSdkVersion="28" />
</manifest>
